text.div:
Encounter Identifier Type Codes

A coded type for an identifier that can be used to determine which identifier to use for a specific purpose (encounter).

This value set includes codes from the following code systems:

  • Include these codes as defined in http://www.interopsante.org/pam-fr/valuesets/identifier-types
    Code Display
    VN Visit Number
    MN Movement Number
  • Include all these codes in http://interopsante.org/fhir/ValueSet/fr-encounter-identifier-type

extension.valueMarkdown: Types are for general categories of identifiers. See [the identifier registry](identifier-registry.h     tml) for a list of common identifier systems
